Program: Free Thinking
Title: British Monarchy Past and Present
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04sv9n7
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 4 Dec 2014
Philip Dodd and a panel including historians Philip Ziegler and John Guy, biographer Sarah Bradford, journalist Deborah Orr and author William Kuhn explore British monarchy past and present and ask what is the role of a royal head of state in the twenty first century. Producer: Harry Parker You can download this programme by searching in the Arts and Ideas podcasts for the broadcast date. Show less